CommonFields.Title: Enhanced dielectric and ferroelectric properties induced by dopamine-modified BaTiO3 nanofibers in flexible poly(vinylidene fluoride-trifluoroethylene) nanocomposites
Author: Song, Yu
Shen, Yang
Liu, Haiyang
Lin, Yuanhua
Li, Ming
Nan, Ce-Wen
CommonFields.Location: Department of Materials Science and Engineering, State Key Lab of New Ceramics and Fine Processing, Tsinghua University, Beijing, China

Mixing.Description: barium acetate, tetrabutyl titanate and acetylacetone at a molar ratio fo 1:1:2 were disolved in acetic acid and stirred to get a homogeneous barium titanate precurosr solution.

Additive.Description: Poly(vinyl pyrrolodione) (PVP, M=1 300 000) was added to the precursor for the control of the solution viscosity.

Mixing.Description: The solution was then transerred into a syringe and electrospun with an applied electric field of 1.5 kV / cm.  Fibers consisted of PVP and barium titanate precursor obtained via electrospinning were calcined at 950 deg C to get BaTiO3 nanofibers.
BaTiO3 nanofibers were dispersed into 0.01 mol / L of dopamine hydrochloride aqueous solution and stirred for 10 h at 60 deg C
poly(vinylidene fluoride-trifluoroethylene) were dispersed in N,N-dimethylformamide (DMF) by ultrasonication for 2 h.

Drying-Evaporation.Description: The as-cast films were dried at 50 deg C for 10 h.

Dielectric_and_Impedance_Spectroscopy_An.Description: The dielectric properties were measured by employing a HP 4294A precision impedance analyzer (Agilent) at room temperature.  The elctric breakdown strength was tested by a dielectric withstand voltage test (Beijing Electromechanical Research Institute Supesvoltage Technique) at a ramping rate of 200 V/s and a limiting current of 5mA.
P-E loops (polarization-electric field loops) were measured by a Premier II ferroelectric test system (Radiant Technologies, Inc.)

Differential_Scanning_Calorimetry.Description: The effect of BaTiO3 nanocomposites was investigated by using differential scanning calorimetry (DSC) with TGA/DSC1 (Metter-Toledo, Switzerland) in a cooling scan from 200 deg C to room temperature ata  cooling rate of 10 deg C / min.
